    <STRONG>Recap:</STRONG> Texas Instruments President and CEO Rich Templeton used a "This is Your Life" format to show the different ways that TI products have affected the guest of honor, the CE consumer. With Fox News Analyst and former pro football player Howie Long, Templeton discussed the impact that digital light processing (DLP) is having on the high-definition TV market. Over 2 million DLP TVs have been sold in the last eight months and they currently represent 40 percent of the front projection television market.<BR><BR>Dreamworks Animation CEO Katzenberg discussed how DLP cinema will impact the movie industry with improved quality in movies, such as the ability to feature over 35 trillion colors. Templeton also brought out the CEO of Sling Media, Blake Krikorian, to display the Slingbox Personal Broadcaster, which allows the consumer to access the TV in their living room from anywhere in the world. The last guest was Bruce Hall, the President of Digital Audio Drive, who is creating autonomous vehicles that drive themselves so that no human interaction is required. All of these innovative and new designs are created through the use of various TI technologies. <BR><BR><A href="/docs/TempletonTranscript.pdf" target=_blank>Transcript (pdf)</A><br><br><br>
